<item>
            <title>[HIVE-25050] Disable &apos;hive.metastore.acid.truncate.usebase&apos; config as it&apos;s introducing backward incompatible change</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25050</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-20137&quot; title=&quot;Truncate for Transactional tables should use base_x&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-20137&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-20137&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces new file metadata and writes it into base files during truncate table operations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there is an older version of HMS running in the cluster that doesn&apos;t contain &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-20137&quot; title=&quot;Truncate for Transactional tables should use base_x&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-20137&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-20137&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it won&apos;t be able to handle the new file metadata and will fail to inspect tables that have been truncated, thereby skipping compacting them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should disable &apos;hive.metastore.acid.truncate.usebase&apos; until we don&apos;t have a fix that addresses the backward incompatibility.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
